reviewText: A precursor to reality tv, like so much other documentary work from the 1960's and 70's. One reason I didn't enjoy this film was because I couldn't hear what the people were saying, the sound was awful. The only parts I could make out were those between Marsha Mason and her friend. Marsha Mason is the only reason to watch this, she stands out as always, too bad they didn't give her more dialogue. Was Mailer trying to copy Warhol? Maysles? Wiseman?
